summary: Wouter is an ecologist, with a professional background in remote sensing and GIS. He holds a B.Sc. in Tropical Forestry, a M.Sc. degree in Forest and Nature Conservation and specialized in resource ecology. He spent five years as a project manager and remote sensing specialist working on the monitoring of land use/cover dynamics, forest monitoring, REDD+ baseline assessments and various spatial risk assessments. As a forest ecologist, he has gained experience in vegetation- and wildlife monitoring, environmental management and complex data analysis. As a project manager and consultant at Face the Future, Wouter works on (agro-)forest project development, -analyses, -valuation and -monitoring as well as REDD+ readiness assessments and REDD+ strategy design.
